snippet.textDisplay:
I love that he's trying to restore his family name but he hasn't a chance. Nobody is a bigger supporter of Cadbury's than me, I am an absolute chocaholic and was heartbroken when they sold out.
But it's owned by Mondelez. The minute he appears on their radar they're not going to take it lightly and they're going to try to swat him with billions of dollars to do so with. They will come at him like a tornado and take every single penny he has. It'll be like China and Hong Kong, they'll just wait it out until the public gets tired of reading about it, and then they'll swoop in on him.
If he had some kind of demonic ferocity and charisma to him, topped with the brains of one of the sharks maybe he could pull it off. I'm sure the public would rally behind him strongly. But let's face it, he does seem a bit wet behind the ears. The fact that he didn't choose Peter, who was clearly burning with passion to be his rival, shows his lack of savvy, and so, much to my chagrin, I'm going to have to say he should probably pack it in.

If you want to know what happend next.

"Cadbury was in the den asking the Dragons for £75k for a 5% share of the business. The money was to be invested in two key areas of the business: developing new products including those using online personalisation, and expanding the Love Cocoa team.
The deal with Tej Lalvani saw Cadbury revert to the infamous wall twice to think about his options before finally accepting £75k for a 15% share. However, following a series of lengthy discussions and having met Lalvani several times after the episode was filmed, Cadbury has since decided to go it alone."

snippet.textDisplay: Lets explore the hypocritical, double standards and slimy sycophantism that curtains their insatiable greed. If that was anyone else saying they wanted to bring back classic British chocolates and had given out half the company so easily, they almost certainly wouldn't have picked him for the show. Check out the eyebrows of greed twitching as it dawns this guy is a Cadbury - what an opportunity for the dragons to get their fingers sticky from not sharing... they look past the stuttering, the lousy pitch, the really bad business practices because of name. Hope it bites them in the rear end, lol, myopic money grabbing brown-nosers.
